-- Stiglitz Has No Indication European Leaders Know What to Do
-- B y   K e v i n   C o s t e l l o e
-- 2012-01-26T17:27:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-26/stiglitz-has-no-indication-european-leaders-know-what-to-do.html
Nobel Prize-winning economist  Joseph
Stiglitz  said that he has no indications “that European leaders
have any sense” of what they need to do to solve the debt
crisis.  Stiglitz, a Columbia University economics professor, spoke
in a Bloomberg television interview today from the  World
Economic Forum  in Davos,  Switzerland .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Costelloe at 
 kcostelloe@bloomberg.net  